5000|$|Coming {{between the}} {{publisher}} and the <b>retail</b> <b>bookseller</b> {{is the important}} distributing agency of the wholesale bookseller. It is {{to him that the}} retailer and libraries look for supplies, as it is impossible to stock all of the books published. Paternoster Row, London, was for over a hundred years the centre of this industry, where retail booksellers, busily engaged in obtaining the books ordered by the book-buying public. It is where the publisher calls first on showing or [...] "subscribing" [...] a new book, a critical process, for by the number thus ordered the fate of a book is sometimes determined. In the United States, Baker & Taylor is a major distributor.|$|E
